Training yourself vs. working with a trainer.
___
As a fitness professional, and someone who has been doing this my whole life it is easy to create my own programs and “train myself.” Or even follow a program on my own. But, there is something really nice and equally beneficial to working with a coach. 
___
This is a bit of a program I did yesterday with @kelvingary 
Could I have done it on my own? Yes. 
Would I have pushed myself to the level I did yesterday? Unlikely. 
Would I have programmed all the exercises and in this order? Hard to say, and mostly not because getting off the assault bike straight into walking lunges was not so fun. 
___
Fitness professionals or otherwise having a fitness coach is a huge benefit. 
They give you a little extra push, Hold you accountable, Notice your form, and so much more. 
___

Four days of core

HALF HOLOW HOLD
2 x 
30 seconds 
20 seconds 
10 seconds 
___
Arm shoulder width, apart, fully extended above the head.
Shoulders off the ground, head neutral
One leg extended into a full hollow, hold one the bent
Make sure lower back stays on the ground(if it comes off, then try to bend both knees)

ARCH HOLD 
6 x 20 seconds 
___
Fully extend arms and feet
Attempt to keep both feet and knees together
Head is neutral
Attempt to come up as high as possible
___

SIDE BEND 
3x 
5-7 each side 
___
I am is fully extended overhead
Initiate the shift from the hips, then reach as far as you can
Torso in 
line with legs 
head is neutral
(if you need to scale, attempt with arms at sides)

TABELTOP 
10 x 15 seconds 
___
Arms shoulder width apart, shoulders over wrists knees over ankles 
hands turned to the side or back based on comfort 
Squeeze glutes and keep hips as high as possible 
Head neutral

Yoga in a geothermal spring.
___
Over 10,000 years in the making, formed when melting snow on the Wasatch Mountains seeped deep within the earth. Two miles below the surface, the earth’s interior heated the water. As it percolated upward, it picked up minerals, which were then deposited on the surface, eventually forming the volcano-shaped limestone deposit.
___
Super calm and peaceful environment for yoga with sounds of the water against the crater walls. Be prepared to challenge your balance with the paddle board. The water is super warm, falling in is definitely part of the experience, it is even built into some of the movements. 
___
@VisitUtah #VisitUtah #ForeverMighty #ad @parkcityyogaadventures @hebervalley

1st time for everything 
___
“The charm of fishing is that it is the pursuit of something that is elusive but attainable, a perpetual series of occasions for hope.” – John Bucha 
___
Spent the day on the water learning how to fly fish with @fishheadsflyshop. Picture this: being on the water with the mountains as your backdrop, loads of sunshine, learning a new skill - you are transported to a special place and a state of mind. I cannot speak more highly about this experience. 
___
Mini recap: Suited up in waders, drove to Provo River, dropped the boat in the water where the levels were too high to actually wade, learnt the techniques to cast, caught 10+ fish (rainbow & brown trout), released the fish, reapplied sunscreen, found a new spot to anchor and learned a new technique for different water speed and depth, float down the river back to base and there you have the BEST DAY! 
___
@hebervalley @VisitUtah #VisitUtah #ForeverMighty #ad #utah #flyfishing #travelblogger

Utah, May 2023
___
Living in Manhattan, I crave nature and the outdoors. Utah delivered. Could not have asked for better weather. Spent the weekend dancing with my bestie, hiking, obsessing over every farm and animal we passed, indulging in incredible dinners and fly fishing. What an experience. 
___
Some of my Recommendations:
▪️ McPolin Farm and Nature Trail - it’s paved and beautiful for walking or biking, especially this season since there was so much snow and a lot of the trails were still covered/or super muddy.
▫️Fly fishing is a must @fishheadsflyshop ask for Jerry @guideriteflyfishing 
▪️Stay @pendryparkcity have dinner @kitarestaurant
▫️Dinner in town @pineconeridge_pc get the filet and bread basket 🧺 
▪️ Hike any of the amazing trails, it is all picturesque and beautiful 
▫️Yoga in a geothermal crater @parkcityyogaadventures
▪️Shop in Park City 
___
@VisitUtah #VisitUtah #ForeverMighty #ad @hebervalley #utah #travel #travelblogger #naturelovers
